The paper proposes a new algorithm for efficient exploration in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The algorithm involves the use of randomized value functions, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the benefits of the algorithm in complex stochastic MDPs, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The algorithm is evaluated on the Arcade Learning Environment, which is a benchmark for artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.CV.
